HEADWORD: Raca
<hw>Ra"ca</hw> <pr>(r⟦amac⟧"k⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"raka`</grk>, from Chaldee <ets>r⟦emac⟧k⟦amac⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
term of reproach used by the Jews of our Savior's time, meaning
⟦ldquo⟧worthless.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whosoever shall say to his brother, <qex>Raca</qex>, shall be in
danger of the council.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. v. 22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Racahout</ent>⟦br⟧
